  m_text: 'Abbey Road Studios formerly EMI Recording Studios was the main recording
    studio used by The Beatles. They used both studios one and two, however they
    recorded most of their songs in studio two which is what this room is based on.
    In 1976 the studio was renamed to Abbey Road Studios after the incredible success
    of their album Abbey Road which release in 1969.

'
